## Description
The circular buffer blocks writers when the buffer is full and blocks readers when
the buffer is empty. Threads are synchronized using Java monitors, ensuring mutual
exclusion and correct coordination between concurrent threads.

This implementation follows the concepts discussed in the module on concurrent
programs and the Java multithreading circular buffer example.
